eleuze in film theory. It asks questions about the universe as metacinema, subjectivity, violence, feminism, monstrosity, and music. Among the contemporary films it discusses within a Deleuzian framework are Strange Days, Fight Club, and Dancer in the Dark.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aCinema and Media Studies. 4aLiterary Studies -- General Criticism and Theory. 4aPhilosophy -- Aesthetics. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080476455140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804764551423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804764551/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles